h-freedom-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elong-haul%20international%20routes%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20hub-to-hub%20flying%20would%20not%20be%20affected.%20Instead%2C%20regional%20flying%20and%20domestic%20mainline%20flights%20that%20do%20not%20fly%20between%20hubs%20would%20be%20cut.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrontier%20Airlines%20CEO%20Barry%20Biffle%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flist-of-airports-cutting-flights-faa-government-shutdown-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ewarned%20passengers%20to%20prepare%20for%20the%20worst%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20%26quot%3BIf%20your%20flight%20is%20canceled%2C%20your%20chances%20of%20being%20stranded%20are%20high%2C%20so%20I%20would%20simply%20have%20a%20backup%20ticket%20on%20another%20airline%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%20a%20LinkedIn%20post.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20most%20cases%2C%20customers%20will%20be%20rebooked%20on%20an%20alternate%20flight%20in%20the%20case%20of%20a%20cancellation.%20Customers%20with%20long%20enough%20delays%20are%20also%20entitled%20to%20compensation%20if%20they%20choose%20not%20to%20fly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20is%20the%20best%20advice%20for%20what%20to%20do%20if%20your%20flight%20is%20disrupted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22358cd60d-8945-4024-bbcf-cd498888e8fc%5C%22%3E1.%20Know%20your%20rights%20as%20an%20airline%20passenger%20in%20the%20US%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224256%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20departure%20board%20on%20October%2010.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F690cf4f721c3f142ebfc3d54%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222837%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAirline%20passengers%20have%20some%20customer%20rights%20in%20the%20US.%3Cp%3ELi%20Rui%2FXinhua%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.transportation.gov%2Findividuals%2Faviation-consumer-protection%2Fflight-delays-cancellations%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Department%20of%20Transportation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20there%20is%20no%20law%20requiring%20US%20airlines%20to%20compensate%20passengers%20for%20disruptions%20caused%20by%20uncontrollable%20events%2C%20such%20as%20weather.%20That%20also%20includes%20air%20traffic%20control%20delays.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20rule%20carriers%20must%20follow%20is%20to%20refund%20customers%20in%20the%20event%20of%20cancellations%2C%20even%20for%20non-controllable%20events.%20And%20that%20does%20not%20mean%20travel%20credits%20or%20vouchers%20%E2%80%94%20it%20must%20be%20cash%2C%20and%20includes%20any%20add-ons%2C%20such%20as%20bags%20or%20seats.%20Government-directed%20flight%20cancellations%20would%20qualify.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20carriers%20do%20not%20owe%20meals%2C%20hotel%20rooms%2C%20or%20financial%20compensation%20for%20shutdown-related%20cancellations%20or%20delays%20%E2%80%94%20because%20the%20cause%20is%20the%20government%2C%20not%20the%20airline.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPassengers%20are%20still%20entitled%20to%20a%20refund%20or%20rebooking%20on%20the%20same%20airline%2C%20but%20carriers%20are%20not%20required%20to%20provide%20additional%20accommodations%20or%20rebook%20on%20another%20airline.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%2C%20like%20American%2C%20Delta%2C%20United%2C%20and%20Frontier%2C%20have%20flexible%20travel%20policies%20in%20place%20amid%20the%20reductions%2C%20allowing%20customers%20to%20change%20or%20cancel%20their%20flights.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20choose%20to%20travel%20but%20your%20flight%20is%20delayed%20or%20canceled%2C%20ask%20the%20airline%20for%20the%20reason%20%E2%80%94%20ideally%20in%20writing%20%E2%80%94%20so%20you%20know%20what%20you're%20entitled%20to.%20Airlines%20have%20different%20policies%20for%20disruptions%20they%20control%2C%20like%20crew%20or%20maintenance%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20DoT's%20Airline%20Customer%20Service%20Dashboard%20%E2%80%94%20launched%20in%202022%20%E2%80%94%20shows%20what%20the%2010%20largest%20US%20airlines%20promise%20in%20those%20cases%2C%20including%20rebookings%2C%20meal%20vouchers%2C%20and%20hotel%20accommodations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225a7f17d4-ff98-45a5-ab82-35e1f5320630%5C%22%3E2.%20Monitor%20your%20airline's%20app%20for%20rebooking%20options%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225696%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Southwest%20mobile%20app.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F690cf4b17f37aa653f558bcd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223797%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMost%20airlines%20allow%20customers%20to%20adjust%20their%20flights%20online.%3Cp%3EJaap%20Arriens%2FNurPhoto%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20a%20flight%20delay%20or%20cancellation%20is%20announced%2C%20expect%20people%20to%20flock%20to%20the%20nearest%20customer%20service%20line%20for%20assistance%2C%20and%20for%20the%20phone%20lines%20to%20clog.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWait%20times%20can%20be%20painfully%20long%2C%20and%20the%20best%20alternatives%20will%20likely%20go%20quickly.%20However%2C%20some%20airlines%20offer%20the%20option%20to%20rebook%20on%20their%20website%20or%20mobile%20app%20and%20waive%20any%20fees%2C%20making%20it%20sometimes%20easier%20to%20make%20changes%20online%20than%20in%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20all%20available%20options%20are%20exhausted%2C%20have%20a%20plan%20B%2C%20such%20as%20waiting%20to%20speak%20with%20a%20live%20agent%2C%20contacting%20the%20airline%20through%20social%20media%2C%20or%20booking%20a%20hotel%20for%20the%20night.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDirect%20messaging%20on%20Facebook%20or%20Twitter%20can%20actually%20serve%20as%20a%20virtual%20placeholder%2C%20and%20you%20may%20hear%20back%20via%20chat%20before%20speaking%20to%20a%20live%20agent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20the%20phone%20numbers%20for%20each%20airline%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAlaska%3A%201-800-252-7522%20or%20text%2082008%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAllegiant%3A%201-702-505-8888%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAmerican%3A%201-800-433-7300%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAvelo%3A%201-